race.comment: VERHOEVEN (3) is fitter for two runs back and just missed last time when beaten a nose this course and distance latest. Ready to win and with the claim looks hard to hold out. PACIFIC WITNESS (11) was well in the market on debut over 1000m on heavy ground and kept coming, finishing fourth and beaten just over a length. Has good upside and liked the way she found the line late. SUNRISE AT KIRRA (9) put together three minors on end before racing over 1400m latest and sitting on speed but didn't finish it off. Back in trip and can atone. SWING LOW (15) is a long time maiden who has mixed distances lately and is coming back from a mile. Best figures measure up though and worth including at odds. NICALBI (2) boxed on fairly to finish midfield on debut. Better for it and has a senior rider go on from the inside draw. Looks an improver.
